President Obama has signed a disaster declaration for the State of Washington following a severe windstorm on August 29, 2015. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected area. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Thomas J. Dargan has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.